x4freetext: Low sensitivity pellicles loaded with different
elements under study were prepared, starting from
Ilford K0 emulsion in gel form. The loaded and unloaded
pellicles were irradiated as stacks. Each stack
consisted of 3 400-mumeter-thick pellicles, with each
pellicle loaded with a different element. The beam
direction was perpendicular to the stack surface for
the fission cross section measurements.
The ionization chamber was used for relative
monitoring of the proton beam.
Natural silver was a constituent of the emulsion.
Uranium, thorium, bismuth and tungsten were loaded into
the emulsion pellicles.
Comment by Compiler: the authors mentioned 238-U and
184-W among the loaded nuclei.
Most likely, 238 and 184 here mean not the pure
isotopes but the average atomic mass for natural
uranium and tungsten loaded.
